<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-827-314  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 827 314.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 30 1989 v6 n43 p10(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mips to provide two sets of binary interfaces. (Mips ComputerSystems Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kovsky, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Mips Computer Systems has signed two agreements which are meant tostandardize source-code- and binary-code-compatible interfaces forapplications written for the company's reduced-instruction-setcomputer (RISC) microprocessors.andP;  Mips has reached an agreementwith AT and T for that company to write an application binaryinterface (ABI) that will make Mips processorsbinary-code-compatible with AT and T's Unix System V Release 4.0.andO;Mips also announced an agreement in which 15 systems vendors haveendorsed the company's Mips Application Interface (MAI), whichwill insure source-code-compatibility between applications writtenfor Mips processors.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   MIPS Computer Systems Inc. (contracts)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Product:   Motif (Graphical user interface) (usage).andO;Topic:     Source CodeCompatibilityReduced-Instruction-Set ComputersProgrammingConsortiaSpecificationsMarketing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Mips To Provide Two Sets of Binary InterfacesandM;SUNNYVALE, Calif.andP;  -- Move over, Sparc International and 88open.andP;  MipsComputer Systems has become the latest RISC chip designer to lead its flockinto the promised land of binary-code-compatible software.andM;Two sets of agreements announced last week by Mips illustrate the company'sintent to establish a set of interfaces that will provide software developerswith a recipe for writing source-code-compatible and binary-code-compatibleapplications for all machines based on Mips RISC processors.andM;In its quest to create yet another class of &quot;shrink-wrapped&quot; softwareapplications, Mips will rival the efforts of the competing consortiums formedby RISC chip suppliers Sun Microsystems and Motorola.andM;The first of Mips' recently announced agreements is a contract with ATandamp;T toconstruct an application binary interface (ABI) for establishing binary-codecompatibility between Mips processors and ATandamp;T's Unix System V Release 4.0.andM;In a related announcement, Mips revealed its Mips Application Interface(MAI), a set of programming interfaces that has been endorsed by 15 systemsvendors that are currently using the Mips RISC chip.andM;MAI will ensure source-code compatibility across all systems based on theMips architecture, said Jim Billmaier, Mips' vice president of marketing forsystem software.andM;The companies endorsing MAI include DEC, Tandem Computers, Silicon Graphics,Stardent, Pyramid Technology, CDC, Groupe Bull and Nixdorf Computer AG.andM;The MAI specification, which is available now, incorporates IEEE Posix as itsoperating system interface, MIT's X Window System as its network windowingenvironment, Motif as its graphical user interface and the Mips LanguageInterfaces.andM;The major difference between Mips' MAI push and the parallel efforts of Sun'sSparc International and Motorola's 88open Consortium lies in the choice of auser interface, according to Billmaier.andM;&quot;In Motorola's case, they have not endorsed a user interface, so it'sincomplete,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;In Sun's case, they have backed a user interface[OpenLook] ...andP;  but it's not the one the industry is widely adopting.&quot;andM;Only Mips has officially championed the Open Software Foundation's Motif userinterface, which has the best chance of achieving wide industry support,Billmaier said.andM;The creation of MAI serves a threefold purpose, he said.andM;&quot;First, we wanted to simplify the task of creating application programs forsystems based on the Mips RISC microprocessor design,&quot; Billmaier said.andO;&quot;Second, we wanted to make it very easy to port programs from one Mips-basedsystem to another.andP;  Finally, we wanted to expand the number of applicationsavailable to end users.&quot;andM;&quot;The Mips ABI [for Unix System V] is the basis for the development andavailability of 'shrink-wrap'-style software portability for Mips machinesfrom manufacturers across the industry,&quot; he said.andM;The agreement with ATandamp;T specifies that the new ABI will also become the basisfor trademarked Unix System V software for the Mips architecture.andP;  Inaddition, the contract stipulates that the Mips ABI will be compatible withother ATandamp;T ABI specifications.andM;The Mips ABI is expected to become available at about the same time assimilar ABIs for the Sparc and Motorola 88000 architectures, in the secondquarter of next year, Billmaier said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>